<DOC><DOCNO> AP881103-0296 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-03-88 1341EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-Britannia-Boeing     11-03 0133</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Britannia-Boeing,0141</SECOND><HEAD>Britannia Airways Orders Boeing Planes</HEAD><DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Britannia Airways has ordered eight long-range767-200 airplanes from Boeing Commercial Airlines and securedoptions for eight more, a Britannia official announced today.   Deliveries in the $500 million order are scheduled to begin inFebruary 1990, according to Dave Hopkins, managing director forBritannia.   ``The order also reflects Britannia's commitment to buying large,superquiet aircraft which will help keep noise levels to a minimumand also ease the problem of congested airspace by carrying morepasssengers in one movement,'' Hopkins said.   In Britannia's seating configuration, the 767-200 will carry 273passengers.   Following its takeover of Orion Airways, Britannia will beoperating a fleet of 37 Boeing 737s and seven 767s.   The announcement brings total orders for the Boeing 767 airplaneto 334.</TEXT></DOC>